{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/HowToUseContainerPool","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftsynapsecontainers\/howtousecontainerpool"]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"title":"How to Use ContainerPool","roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"SwiftSynapseContainers"}]},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Pre-warm a pool of MicroVMs for near-instant parallel agent execution.","type":"text"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Essentials","anchor":"Essentials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/ContainerSandboxGuide","doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/SecureProductionGuide","doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/HowToContainerizeAnAgent"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/ContainerPool"},{"text":" eliminates VM boot latency on hot paths. Instead of booting a fresh VM per request, the pool keeps ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"N"},{"text":" pre-warmed VMs ready for immediate allocation. This is essential for multi-agent crews, sub-agent spawning, and any workload where parallel container execution matters.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Requires the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ContainerPool"},{"text":" trait — included in the default ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SecureProduction"},{"text":" bundle.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Basic-Pool-Setup","text":"Basic Pool Setup","type":"heading"},{"code":["\/\/ Create a pool of 4 pre-warmed containers","let pool = ContainerPool(size: 4, config: .strict(image: \"swift:latest\"))","","\/\/ Boot all VMs in parallel — call once at app startup","await pool.prewarm()"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Pre-warming boots all ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"size"},{"text":" VMs concurrently. Call it once, early in your app lifecycle, so VMs are ready before the first request arrives.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Allocating-and-Releasing","text":"Allocating and Releasing","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/ContainerPool\/withContainer(_:)"},{"text":" for automatic release — even if the body throws:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let result = try await pool.withContainer { manager in","    try await manager.run(goal: goal) { goal in","        try await myAgent.execute(goal: goal)","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For manual control:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let manager = await pool.allocate()","defer { Task { await pool.release(manager) } }","","let result = try await manager.run(goal: goal) { goal in","    try await myAgent.execute(goal: goal)","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the pool is empty when ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"allocate()"},{"text":" is called, the caller suspends until another caller releases a manager. Use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/ContainerPool\/tryAllocate()"},{"text":" for non-blocking allocation that returns ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":" when the pool is empty.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Parallel-Multi-Agent-Execution","text":"Parallel Multi-Agent Execution","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/ContainerPool"},{"text":" is designed for structured concurrency. Allocate multiple containers concurrently with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"async let"},{"text":" or a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TaskGroup"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/ Three agents in three isolated VMs, concurrently:","async let r1 = pool.withContainer { m in try await m.run(goal: task1, execute: agent1.execute) }","async let r2 = pool.withContainer { m in try await m.run(goal: task2, execute: agent2.execute) }","async let r3 = pool.withContainer { m in try await m.run(goal: task3, execute: agent3.execute) }","let results = try await [r1, r2, r3]"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"With a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TaskGroup"},{"text":" for dynamic concurrency:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let tasks: [String] = loadTasks()","var outputs: [ContainerizedResult<String>] = []","","try await withThrowingTaskGroup(of: ContainerizedResult<String>.self) { group in","    for task in tasks {","        group.addTask {","            try await pool.withContainer { manager in","                try await manager.run(goal: task) { goal in","                    try await myAgent.execute(goal: goal)","                }","            }","        }","    }","    for try await result in group {","        outputs.append(result)","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Sizing-the-Pool","text":"Sizing the Pool","type":"heading"},{"rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Scenario"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Recommended pool size"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Single agent, occasional use"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1 (no pool needed — use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ContainerManager"},{"type":"text","text":" directly)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Single agent, frequent requests"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"2–3"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Multi-agent crew, fixed parallelism N"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"N"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Dynamic sub-agent spawning"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"max expected concurrent sub-agents"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"type":"table","header":"row"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Check ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"await pool.availableCount"},{"text":" at runtime to observe pool utilization.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Checking-Pool-Capacity","text":"Checking Pool Capacity","type":"heading"},{"code":["let total     = await pool.capacity        \/\/ always equals the size passed to init","let available = await pool.availableCount  \/\/ currently idle VMs","let inUse     = total - available"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Important-Notes","text":"Important Notes","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Pre-warm before serving requests."}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"allocate()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" on an unwarmed pool will suspend indefinitely if the pool has no managers ("},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/ContainerPool\/tryAllocate()","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" returns "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instead of suspending)."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Pools are actor-isolated."}]},{"type":"text","text":" All "},{"code":"allocate()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"release()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"code":"withContainer(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" calls are safe to call concurrently from any number of tasks."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Release on cancellation."}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"withContainer(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" uses "},{"code":"defer","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to release the manager even when the task is cancelled. For manual "},{"code":"allocate()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" calls, use "},{"code":"defer { Task { await pool.release(manager) } }","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://SwiftSynapseContainers/documentation/SwiftSynapseContainers/HowToContainerizeAnAgent":{"type":"topic","role":"article","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiftsynapsecontainers\/howtocontainerizeanagent","abstract":[{"text":"Step-by-step guide to adding ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Containerized","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to an existing ","type":"text"},{"code":"@SpecDrivenAgent","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" actor.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/HowToContainerizeAnAgent","title":"How to Containerize an Agent"},"doc://SwiftSynapseContainers/documentation/SwiftSynapseContainers/SecureProductionGuide":{"url":"\/documentation\/swiftsynapsecontainers\/secureproductionguide","kind":"article","title":"Secure Production Guide","role":"article","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Deploy containerized agents with credential injection, real-time monitoring, and container state persistence."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/SecureProductionGuide"},"doc://SwiftSynapseContainers/documentation/SwiftSynapseContainers/GettingStarted":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/GettingStarted","title":"Getting Started with SwiftSynapseContainers","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftsynapsecontainers\/gettingstarted","kind":"article","role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"From a standard SwiftSynapse agent to a hardware-isolated MicroVM agent in four steps."}]},"doc://SwiftSynapseContainers/documentation/SwiftSynapseContainers/ContainerPool/withContainer(_:)":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/ContainerPool\/withContainer(_:)","url":"\/documentation\/swiftsynapsecontainers\/containerpool\/withcontainer(_:)","kind":"symbol","title":"withContainer(_:)","type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"withContainer","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"T","kind":"genericParameter"},{"kind":"text","text":">(("},{"text":"ContainerManager","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:22SwiftSynapseContainers16ContainerManagerC"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"text":"async","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"T"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"async"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"T"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Allocates a container, runs "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"body"},{"type":"text","text":", and releases it — even if "},{"code":"body","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" throws.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SwiftSynapseContainers/documentation/SwiftSynapseContainers/ContainerSandboxGuide":{"abstract":[{"text":"A complete reference for the SwiftSynapseContainers runtime — configuration, lifecycle, security policies, and the relationship between host and guest.","type":"text"}],"title":"Container Sandbox Guide","kind":"article","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiftsynapsecontainers\/containersandboxguide","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/ContainerSandboxGuide","type":"topic"},"doc://SwiftSynapseContainers/documentation/SwiftSynapseContainers":{"url":"\/documentation\/swiftsynapsecontainers","kind":"symbol","title":"SwiftSynapseContainers","role":"collection","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Hardware-enforced MicroVM sandbox isolation for SwiftSynapse agents — true per-agent security via Apple’s Virtualization.framework."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers"},"doc://SwiftSynapseContainers/documentation/SwiftSynapseContainers/ContainerPool/tryAllocate()":{"url":"\/documentation\/swiftsynapsecontainers\/containerpool\/tryallocate()","kind":"symbol","title":"tryAllocate()","role":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Returns nil if a manager is immediately available, nil otherwise (non-blocking).","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/documentation\/SwiftSynapseContainers\/ContainerPool\/tryAllocate()","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"tryAllocate"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ContainerManager","preciseIdentifier":"s:22SwiftSynapseContainers16ContainerManagerC"},{"kind":"text","text":"?"}]},"doc://SwiftSynapseContainers/documentation/SwiftSynapseC